# Decision log

Time-ordered log of decisions per Purpose / cycle. Used to trace why a hypothesis was
dropped, why a Purpose was opened or split off, or why a particular method was chosen,
after the fact.

A "cycle" here is one notebook (= one Purpose). A Purpose with multiple H's
yields a single cycle entry with H sub-bullets, not one entry per H.

## Format

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD cycle <N> (exp_<NNN>_<purpose-slug>) — Purpose: <one-line>

- **Tested H<id>**: [one-line restatement]
  - Observation: [observed values, anomalies]
  - Verdict: [supported / rejected / partial / parked]
  - Robustness battery (this H): [pass / fail per item in robustness_battery.md]
- **Tested H<id+1> (derived from H<id>, same Purpose)**: [one-line restatement]
  - Observation: ...
  - Verdict: ...
  - Robustness battery (this H): ...
- **Tested H<id+2>** (...): ...

- **Purpose-level synthesis**: [one or two sentences across all H's tested]

- **Derived hypotheses for this Purpose** (= future H rounds in this notebook):
  - H<new> (run-now): ...
  - H<new> (next-session): ...

- **Derived Purposes** (= candidates for new notebooks):
  - P<new> (run-now): ...
  - P<new> (next-session): ...

- **Direction rejected**: [what was tried inside this Purpose and did not work,
  with reason]
```

## Example

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD cycle 5 (exp_005_mean_reversion_eurusd_intraday) — Purpose: does mean-reversion work on EUR/USD intraday?

- **Tested H3**: entry filter × signal-flip exit beats fee 0.5 bp/side
  - Observation:
    - val Sharpe +0.52 (fee 1 bp), +1.45 (fee 0)
    - win 62.4 % (val) / 62.3 % (test) — preserved across the split
    - Walk-forward mean Sharpe -0.10, pct_positive 47.4 % (unstable)
    - Bootstrap 95 % CI = [0.009, 0.202], p = 0.014 — significant but small effect size
  - Verdict: partial (negative at fee 1 bp, borderline at 0.5 bp, walk-forward unstable)
  - Robustness battery (H3): 4 of 7 passed (threshold ✓ / fee ✓ / bootstrap CI border /
    walk-forward ✗ / DSR not computed / realistic cost not run / regime not run)

- **Tested H10 (derived from H3, same Purpose)**: vol-targeted size to stabilize walk-forward
  - Observation: walk-forward pct_positive 0.474 → 0.71, val Sharpe slightly down (1.45 → 1.18)
    at fee 0; test Sharpe 0.62 → 0.55
  - Verdict: supported (walk-forward stability gate met; test Sharpe acceptable)
  - Robustness battery (H10): 6 of 7 passed (regime not run)

- **Purpose-level synthesis**: mean-reversion works on EUR/USD intraday only with
  vol-targeted sizing (H10); fixed sizing (H3) is fragile across walk-forward windows.

- **Derived hypotheses for this Purpose**:
  - H12 (run-now): regime-conditional Sharpe (trending vs. ranging) on H10's strategy
  - H13 (next-session): multi-asset generalization within FX majors

- **Derived Purposes**:
  - P_momentum_eurusd_intraday (run-now): is the inverse phenomenon (continuation)
    profitable on the same universe? Different phenomenon, so a new notebook.
  - P_meanrev_jpypairs (next-session): same Purpose grain on JPY-cross intraday;
    different cross-section ⇒ new notebook.

- **Direction rejected**: time-stop alone as exit (effect size < fee). Reason: signal
  horizon and exit horizon do not coincide.
```

## Notes

- Do not delete. Negative results stay.
- Use specific numbers ("Sharpe -1.74" rather than "Sharpe was low")
- Always classify derived hypotheses (run-now / next-session / drop)
- Always classify derived Purposes (run-now / next-session / drop)
- Per-Purpose entries replace the older per-H entries; multiple H's belong as
  sub-bullets under one Purpose entry
